main event: A civilian observed a bright, metallic, round object reflecting sunlight in the Miami, Florida area for about 10 minutes in June 1964.
interesting points: The object was yellowish-red in color and appeared to be hovering at the same altitude as nearby aircraft at 16,000 feet.
The witness stated that the object would not likely have been observed unless the conditions were just right.
No other corroborating reports were received, and the case was marked as INSUFFICIENT DATA to determine if the sighting constituted a valid UFO.
The witness requested information on the results of the investigation, but no photographs were submitted.
The report includes some handwritten notes and calculations, but their significance is unclear.
sighted object: A bright, metallic, round object reflecting sunlight
